Sentencas: A novel, microchanneled tubular solid oxide fuel cell was fabricated using a multipass extrusion process, with an outside diameter of 2.7 mm that contained 61 cells.
Titulo: Novel design of microchanneled tubular solid oxide fuel cells and synthesis using a multipass extrusion process

Sentencas: Cell materials used in this work were 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia (8YSZ), La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 (LSM), and NiO-8YSZ (50:50 vol%) as electrolyte, cathode, and anode, respectively.
Titulo: Novel design of microchanneled tubular solid oxide fuel cells and synthesis using a multipass extrusion process

Sentencas: Three stages of heat-treatment processes were applied, at 700 degrees C in N-2 condition, at 1000 degrees C in air, and then sintered at 1300 degrees C for 2 h, respectively.
Titulo: Novel design of microchanneled tubular solid oxide fuel cells and synthesis using a multipass extrusion process

Sentencas: The X-ray diffraction analysis confirmed that no reaction phases appeared after sintering.
Titulo: Novel design of microchanneled tubular solid oxide fuel cells and synthesis using a multipass extrusion process

Sentencas: The microstructures of anode and cathode were fairly porous while the electrolyte had a dense microstructure (relative density > 96%).
Titulo: Novel design of microchanneled tubular solid oxide fuel cells and synthesis using a multipass extrusion process

Sentencas: The thickness of electrolyte, anode, and cathode were 20, 30, and 40 mu m, respectively, and the diameter of the continuous channels was 150 mu m.
Titulo: Novel design of microchanneled tubular solid oxide fuel cells and synthesis using a multipass extrusion process
